nodes.bodyText:
You shouldn't need to check these permissions manually in Java Code.  You can still use a @PreAuthorize annotation on this method by doing:
@PreAuthorize("hasPermission(#groupId, 'GROUP', 'READ') or hasAuthority('ADMIN')")
If you look at how hasPermission is defined for GROUP Read privileges, you'll see it's actually just returning true whenever you are a member of the group: https://github.com/DSpace/DSpace/blob/master/dspace-server-webapp/src/main/java/org/dspace/app/rest/security/GroupRestPermissionEvaluatorPlugin.java#L67-L69

